<article>
    <h1>6,200 get poly places via early ad&#xAD;mis&#xAD;sions</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20210104/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2021-01-04"><time>2021-01-04</time></a>
        - <span>FRONT PAGE</span>
        - <span role="byline">San&#xAD;dra Davie Se&#xAD;nior Ed&#xAD;u&#xAD;ca&#xAD;tion Cor&#xAD;re&#xAD;spon&#xAD;dent</span>
    </section>

    <p>Jan­uary is “re­sults month” for Olevel school leavers and stu­dents tak­ing their fi­nal ex­am­i­na­tions at the In­sti­tute of Tech­ni­cal Ed­u­ca­tion (ITE). For about 6,200 of them though, it will be a less anxious wait – they have al­ready been of­fered polytech­nic places for April through the Early Ad­mis­sions Ex­er­cise (EAE).</p>
    <p>Min­istry of Ed­u­ca­tion (MOE) fig­ures show that a record num­ber of 15,400 O-level school leavers and ITE stu­dents ap­plied for polytech­nic places through the EAE last year.</p>
    <p>In 2019, 13,800 se­condary school and ITE stu­dents had ap­plied and 6,000 of them re­ceived of­fers.</p>
    <p>The of­fers came even be­fore the stu­dents re­ceive their fi­nal ex­ami</p>
    <p>De­spite the deep­est re­ces­sion since Sin­ga­pore’s in­de­pen­dence in 1965, Sin­ga­pore­ans dipped deep into their pock­ets to give record sums to char­ity through on­line plat­forms last year. With the shadow of the pan­demic hang­ing over the na­tion, Giv­ing.sg re­ceived more than</p>
    <p>$84 mil­lion last year – over twice the sum it col­lected in 2019.</p>

